-- Turkish Stocks: Akfen, Tupras, Ipek, Yapi Kredi Sigorta Move
-- B y   S i b e l   A k b a y
-- 2012-06-27T15:55:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/turkish-stocks-akfen-tupras-ipek-yapi-kredi-sigorta-move.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 1.8 percent to 61,184.33 at the close in Istanbul,
paring its quarterly decline to 2 percent. The gauge is up 19
percent for the year.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Akfen Holding AS (AKFEN)  , a Turkish builder, added 2.5
percent, the biggest rise since April 26, to 9.16 liras, after
its unit TAV Insaat said it won an auction to build a terminal
at Abu Dhabi Airport at a cost of more than $3 billion with
partners.  Ipek Dogal Enerji Kaynaklari Arastirma & Uretim AS (IPEKE
TI), a Turkish energy company, advanced 4.6 percent to 3.86
liras, after saying it started oil exploration at a site in the
southeastern province of Batman. The company’s shares surged as
much as 8.7 percent in intraday trading to the highest level
since listing in June 2000.  Tupras Turkiye Petrol Rafinerileri AS (TUPRS)  , Turkey’s
oil refiner, climbed for a second day, up 2.2 percent at 37.10
liras, the biggest gain in two weeks, after  ING Groep NV (INGA) 
included the company in its top picks.  Yapi Kredi Bankasi AS (YKBNK TI), the Turkish bank part-
owned by  UniCredit SpA (UCG) , jumped 5 percent to 3.66 liras, the
highest in almost three months, after the lender said it was
evaluating the possibility of selling stakes in units  Yapi Kredi
Sigorta AS (YKSGR)  and Yapi Kredi Emeklilik AS.  Yapi Kredi Sigorta AS (YKSGR TI), a Turkish insurance
company, surged to the highest level in more than a year, up 9.4
percent to 17.4 liras, after parent Yapi & Kredi Bankasi AS said
it is assessing options to sell a stake in the unit. The stock
is up 13 percent in the second quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
